    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sr-(Tripeptide-118 s-Sheep Polypeptide-1 s-Pseudomonas phage phiKZ Polypeptide-1 Dipeptide-19 Hexapeptide-40) is a single chain recombinant peptide produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from Tripeptide-118, s-Sheep Polypeptide-1, s-Pseudomonas Phage phiKZ Polypeptide-1, Dipeptide-19, and Hexapeptide-40. The fusion peptide contains 280 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 amino acids."
    ],
